{
  "message": "test(fuzz,bd-4znjn): add coverage-guided harness for parse_time_input\n\nsrc/ui/time_parser.rs:11 parse_time_input(&str) -> Option<i64> is\nexercised by config_input.rs (4 sites), wizard.rs (3 sites), and\nother UI surfaces accepting free-text time expressions. The vmtms\nregression suite pinned a finite list of adversarial inputs, but no\ncoverage-guided fuzz harness existed.\n\nThis adds fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_time_parser.rs (crash-detector\narchetype): bound input to 8KB, decode as UTF-8, call\nparse_time_input. Harness MUST observe the totality invariant \u2014\nSome(i64) or None, never panic. Seed corpus has 23 entries covering\nrelative durations (-7d, 24h, 30m, 1w), keywords (now, today,\nyesterday, '30 days ago', '2 weeks ago'), absolute dates (ISO,\nslash, dash variants), unix timestamps (s/ms cutoff), adversarial\ninputs (empty, whitespace, multibyte UTF-8 emoji, '-' alone,\n9999-99-99).\n\nCloses coding_agent_session_search-4znjn.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
